  "text": "MP joint instability is an important outcome measurement in the article of de [CITATION_1] . Failure to correct MP joint instability will affect the quality of function at the CMC joint, particularly motion in palmar abduction and opposition, no matter which opposition transfer is used. Interestingly, their transfer of flexor digitorum superficialis failed to provide MP joint stability by their definition in 60% of grade 3A thumbs.",
